data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
Configure your URL types in the app.config file. There are three parts to a setting - the custom protocol, the application path and the "true" protocol.
These settings are stored in the form: CustomProtocol=Application Path,Protocol
For example, to handle URIs with a new protocol called "cisco" you might define a setting as shown: cisco=C:\Program Files\PuTTY\putty.exe,ssh
Calling this application with the command line cisco://10.1.4.54 would then cause this application to run: C:\Program Files\PuTTY\putty.exe ssh://10.1.4.54
